{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":988,"text":"When I wrote my memoir,"},{"time":2889,"text":"the publishers were really confused."},{"time":6566,"text":"Was it about me as a child refugee,"},{"time":10800,"text":"or as a woman who set up a high-tech\nsoftware company back in the 1960s,"},{"time":16304,"text":"one that went public"},{"time":18380,"text":"and eventually employed over 8,500 people?"},{"time":22963,"text":"Or was it as a mother\nof an autistic child?"},{"time":27470,"text":"Or as a philanthropist that's\nnow given away serious money?"},{"time":31925,"text":"Well, it turns out, I'm all of these."},{"time":34569,"text":"So let me tell you my story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39779,"text":"All that I am stems from when\nI got onto a train in Vienna,"},{"time":46446,"text":"part of the Kindertransport that saved\nnearly 10,000 Jewish children"},{"time":51483,"text":"from Nazi Europe."},{"time":53851,"text":"I was five years old, clutching the hand\nof my nine-year-old sister"},{"time":57860,"text":"and had very little idea as to \nwhat was going on."},{"time":61813,"text":"\"What is England and \nwhy am I going there?\""},{"time":66504,"text":"I'm only alive because so long ago, \nI was helped by generous strangers."},{"time":74911,"text":"I was lucky, and doubly lucky\nto be later reunited"},{"time":78446,"text":"with my birth parents."},{"time":80885,"text":"But, sadly, I never bonded \nwith them again."},{"time":87917,"text":"But I've done more in the seven decades\nsince that miserable day \n"},{"time":91227,"text":"when my mother put me on the train"},{"time":93003,"text":"than I would ever have dreamed possible."},{"time":96290,"text":"And I love England, my adopted country,"},{"time":99398,"text":"with a passion that perhaps only someone\nwho has lost their human rights can feel."},{"time":105831,"text":"I decided to make mine a life\nthat was worth saving."},{"time":112188,"text":"And then, I just got on with it."},{"time":115709,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":119264,"text":"Let me take you back to the early 1960s."},{"time":123465,"text":"To get past the gender issues of the time,"},{"time":127953,"text":"I set up my own software house at one\nof the first such startups in Britain."},{"time":134443,"text":"But it was also a company of women,\na company for women,"},{"time":140301,"text":"an early social business."},{"time":143325,"text":"And people laughed at the very idea\nbecause software, at that time,"},{"time":147001,"text":"was given away free with hardware."},{"time":149074,"text":"Nobody would buy software,\ncertainly not from a woman."},{"time":153808,"text":"Although women were then coming out\nof the universities with decent degrees,"},{"time":159745,"text":"there was a glass ceiling to our progress."},{"time":164309,"text":"And I'd hit that glass ceiling too often,"},{"time":168985,"text":"and I wanted opportunities for women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172550,"text":"I recruited professionally qualified women\nwho'd left the industry on marriage,"},{"time":177042,"text":"or when their first child was expected"},{"time":179293,"text":"and structured them into a\nhome-working organization."},{"time":184484,"text":"We pioneered the concept of women\ngoing back into the workforce"},{"time":189069,"text":"after a career break."},{"time":191611,"text":"We pioneered all sorts of\nnew, flexible work methods:"},{"time":195394,"text":"job shares, profit-sharing, \nand eventually, co-ownership"},{"time":200646,"text":"when I took a quarter of the company\ninto the hands of the staff"},{"time":204092,"text":"at no cost to anyone but me."},{"time":209582,"text":"For years, I was the first woman this,\nor the only woman that."},{"time":215773,"text":"And in those days, I couldn't work\non the stock exchange,"},{"time":219539,"text":"I couldn't drive a bus or fly an airplane."},{"time":223300,"text":"Indeed, I couldn't open a bank account\nwithout my husband's permission."},{"time":229193,"text":"My generation of women fought\nthe battles for the right to work"},{"time":233715,"text":"and the right for equal pay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238207,"text":"Nobody really expected much \nfrom people at work or in society"},{"time":242068,"text":"because all the expectations then \n"},{"time":244566,"text":"were about home and \nfamily responsibilities."},{"time":248461,"text":"And I couldn't really face that,"},{"time":251298,"text":"so I started to challenge\nthe conventions of the time,"},{"time":257287,"text":"even to the extent of changing my name\nfrom \"Stephanie\" to \"Steve\""},{"time":263142,"text":"in my business development letters,"},{"time":264891,"text":"so as to get through the door\nbefore anyone realized"},{"time":267369,"text":"that he was a she."},{"time":268750,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272054,"text":"My company, called Freelance Programmers,\nand that's precisely what it was,"},{"time":279214,"text":"couldn't have started smaller: \non the dining room table,"},{"time":284287,"text":"and financed by the equivalent\nof 100 dollars in today's terms,"},{"time":289681,"text":"and financed by my labor and \nby borrowing against the house."},{"time":296978,"text":"My interests were scientific, \nthe market was commercial --"},{"time":302615,"text":"things such as payroll,\nwhich I found rather boring."},{"time":306640,"text":"So I had to compromise with \noperational research work,"},{"time":311752,"text":"which had the intellectual challenge \nthat interested me"},{"time":315183,"text":"and the commercial value \nthat was valued by the clients:"},{"time":322850,"text":"things like scheduling freight trains,"},{"time":328108,"text":"time-tabling buses, stock control,\nlots and lots of stock control."},{"time":334297,"text":"And eventually, the work came in."},{"time":338545,"text":"We disguised the domestic and\npart-time nature of the staff"},{"time":342300,"text":"by offering fixed prices,\none of the very first to do so."},{"time":347440,"text":"And who would have guessed\nthat the programming"},{"time":350755,"text":"of the black box flight recorder \nof Supersonic Concord"},{"time":354699,"text":"would have been done by a bunch \nof women working in their own homes."},{"time":359908,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":367392,"text":"All we used was a simple \n\"trust the staff\" approach"},{"time":372323,"text":"and a simple telephone."},{"time":374504,"text":"We even used to ask job applicants, \n\"Do you have access to a telephone?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":382175,"text":"An early project was to develop\nsoftware standards"},{"time":385194,"text":"on management control protocols."},{"time":387434,"text":"And software was and still is a\nmaddeningly hard-to-control activity,"},{"time":393636,"text":"so that was enormously valuable."},{"time":395747,"text":"We used the standards ourselves,"},{"time":397971,"text":"we were even paid to update \nthem over the years,"},{"time":400989,"text":"and eventually, they were adopted by NATO."},{"time":406323,"text":"Our programmers -- remember, only women,"},{"time":410450,"text":"including gay and transgender --"},{"time":413896,"text":"worked with pencil and paper\nto develop flowcharts"},{"time":418939,"text":"defining each task to be done."},{"time":422596,"text":"And they then wrote code, \nusually machine code,"},{"time":426509,"text":"sometimes binary code,"},{"time":428776,"text":"which was then sent\nby mail to a data center"},{"time":433506,"text":"to be punched onto\npaper tape or card"},{"time":437724,"text":"and then re-punched, \nin order to verify it."},{"time":442051,"text":"All this, before it ever got\nnear a computer."},{"time":445387,"text":"That was programming in the early 1960s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451566,"text":"In 1975, 13 years from startup,"},{"time":456701,"text":"equal opportunity legislation \ncame in in Britain"},{"time":459912,"text":"and that made it illegal to have \nour pro-female policies."},{"time":466824,"text":"And as an example of \nunintended consequences,"},{"time":470400,"text":"my female company had to let the men in."},{"time":474072,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479014,"text":"When I started my company of women,"},{"time":481418,"text":"the men said, \"How interesting, because\nit only works because it's small.\""},{"time":488317,"text":"And later, as it became sizable, \nthey accepted, \"Yes, it is sizable now,"},{"time":494136,"text":"but of no strategic interest.\""},{"time":498125,"text":"And later, when it was a company\nvalued at over three billion dollars,"},{"time":505274,"text":"and I'd made 70 of the staff \ninto millionaires,"},{"time":509877,"text":"they sort of said, \"Well done, Steve!\""},{"time":513397,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":517683,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521969,"text":"You can always tell ambitious women\nby the shape of our heads:"},{"time":526255,"text":"They're flat on top for being \npatted patronizingly."},{"time":529580,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":535521,"text":"And we have larger feet to stand\naway from the kitchen sink."},{"time":540084,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":541737,"text":"Let me share with you \ntwo secrets of success:"},{"time":545562,"text":"Surround yourself with first-class people\nand people that you like;"},{"time":551781,"text":"and choose your partner\nvery, very carefully."},{"time":558065,"text":"Because the other day when I said, \n\"My husband's an angel,\""},{"time":561278,"text":"a woman complained --\n\"You're lucky,\" she said,"},{"time":563764,"text":"\"mine's still alive.\""},{"time":565790,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":573117,"text":"If success were easy, \nwe'd all be millionaires."},{"time":579054,"text":"But in my case, it came in the midst\nof family trauma and indeed, crisis."},{"time":589258,"text":"Our late son, Giles, was an only child,\na beautiful, contented baby."},{"time":597532,"text":"And then, at two and a half,"},{"time":601465,"text":"like a changeling in a fairy story,"},{"time":604738,"text":"he lost the little speech that he had"},{"time":608170,"text":"and turned into a wild, \nunmanageable toddler."},{"time":613442,"text":"Not the terrible twos;"},{"time":615524,"text":"he was profoundly autistic \nand he never spoke again."},{"time":624387,"text":"Giles was the first resident in the first\nhouse of the first charity that I set up"},{"time":629734,"text":"to pioneer services for autism."},{"time":633304,"text":"And then there's been\na groundbreaking Prior's Court school"},{"time":636304,"text":"for pupils with autism"},{"time":638724,"text":"and a medical research charity,\nagain, all for autism."},{"time":642844,"text":"Because whenever I found a gap\nin services, I tried to help."},{"time":649313,"text":"I like doing new things \nand making new things happen."},{"time":654583,"text":"And I've just started a three-year \nthink tank for autism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661159,"text":"And so that some of my wealth does go back\nto the industry from which it stems,"},{"time":666434,"text":"I've also founded \nthe Oxford Internet Institute"},{"time":670017,"text":"and other IT ventures."},{"time":672510,"text":"The Oxford Internet Institute\nfocuses not on the technology,"},{"time":676795,"text":"but on the social, economic, legal\nand ethical issues of the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683887,"text":"Giles died unexpectedly 17 years ago now."},{"time":690909,"text":"And I have learned to live without him,"},{"time":694689,"text":"and I have learned to live \nwithout his need of me."},{"time":699469,"text":"Philanthropy is all that I do now."},{"time":702829,"text":"I need never worry about getting lost"},{"time":705188,"text":"because several charities\nwould quickly come and find me."},{"time":708697,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":720807,"text":"It's one thing to have an idea \nfor an enterprise,"},{"time":724885,"text":"but as many people in this room will know,"},{"time":727112,"text":"making it happen is a very difficult thing"},{"time":730025,"text":"and it demands extraordinary energy,\nself-belief and determination,"},{"time":738117,"text":"the courage to risk family and home,"},{"time":742322,"text":"and a 24/7 commitment \nthat borders on the obsessive."},{"time":747491,"text":"So it's just as well\nthat I'm a workaholic."},{"time":751475,"text":"I believe in the beauty of work when we\ndo it properly and in humility."},{"time":758153,"text":"Work is not just something I do\nwhen I'd rather be doing something else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765612,"text":"We live our lives forward."},{"time":767756,"text":"So what has all that taught me?"},{"time":772210,"text":"I learned that tomorrow's \nnever going to be like today,"},{"time":775846,"text":"and certainly nothing like yesterday."},{"time":778899,"text":"And that made me able to cope with change,"},{"time":782306,"text":"indeed, eventually to welcome change,"},{"time":786634,"text":"though I'm told I'm still very difficult."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791666,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793801,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}